Ingersoll-Rand Boosts Dividend 71%, Plans $2 Billion Buyback

-- B y   E d   D u f n e r
-- 
2011-04-07T11:37:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-07/ingersoll-rand-boosts-dividend-71-plans-2-billion-buyback-1-.html
Ingersoll-Rand Plc (IR) , the maker of
Trane air conditioners, raised its dividend 71 percent to 12
cents a share and authorized buying back as much as $2 billion
in stock.  The dividend is payable June 30 to shareholders of record
on June 17, the Swords, Ireland-based company said today in a
statement. The previous payout was 7 cents a share. The dividend
was projected to rise to 16 cents, based on Bloomberg data.  The shares rose 20 cents to $48.02 at 7 a.m. before New
York Stock Exchange composite trading.  Ingersoll-Rand had 329.6 million shares outstanding as of
Feb. 11, according to data compiled by Bloomberg. At yesterdayâ€™s
closing price, a $2 billion repurchase would amount to about
41.8 million shares.  To contact the reporter on this story:
